text: You know I still can't believe

that I had no idea
that you liked Reggie.
Well, we have a lot in common.
Like science and, um...
Science.

Well, I'm sure he'll be
a great boyfriend.

Ooh, we can go
on double dates together.

Whoa, whoa.
Reggie is not my boyfriend.
Mm. Yet.

Just wait until you two
are slow dancing together

and you get lost
in each other's eyes,
and he kisses you.

On the dance floor?
In front of everyone?
Stop worrying, Ames.

You don't have to kiss him
if you don't want to.

Mom:
Girls, the boys are here.
Okay. You good?

I'm just second-guessing
this sub-color.
I'll be down in a minute.
You look beautiful.

- You look nice.
- Thank you.

- What about me?
- You got something

- on your cheek.
- I do?

Yeah.
You look better than nice.

They make a cute couple,
don't they?
Not as cute as us, though.

Okay, everyone. Enough talking.
Let's get some photos.
Ooh, not without Amy.

Holly:
Amy! Hey, Amy! We need you.

Just scooch a little closer.
You guys look so amazing.

Okay, is there supposed
to be a filter on these things?

- I don't know what it is.
- Dad: What's a filter?
Oh!

- Oh!
- ( squealing )

- You look so beautiful.
- Great.

Shouldn't you be standing
with your date?
Right.

- Hey, Reggie.
- Hi.
Oh. Thanks.

Okay, everyone,
a little bit closer
and on three, two, one.
Pickle!

- Okay. I think I got it.
- That looks great.

- Let's roll.
- Come on, Holly.

- You got the keys?
- ( overlapping chatter )
( wind howling, thunder )

- Oof.
- We're going to get soaked.
Amy: It won't matter.

The dance has been canceled
because of the weather.

We should all just try to get
home before it gets worse.
It already has.
The roads are out for flooding.
You're all stuck here.
